-- Turkish President Approves Law to Allow Court Defense in Kurdish
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2013-01-30T18:50:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-30/turkish-president-approves-law-to-allow-court-defense-in-kurdish.html
Turkish President  Abdullah Gul 
approved a law that allows suspects to defend themselves in
their mother tongue, including the once-banned Kurdish language,
state-run Anatolia news agency says today.
* NOTE: The move comes amid talks between Turkish officials and
imprisoned PKK chief Abdullah Ocalan to try to end fighting by
PKK militants for autonomy in the countryâ€™s Kurdish-dominated
